<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="216" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,968,2039]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1292,1319]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennal flagellum wide. Posterior margin of scutum without black band. Posterior margin of scutellum and abdominal tergites 3–6 with pale yellow setae. Lateral margin of male gonocoxite slightly curved subapically; apex of epiphallus bifid, branch slender and acute apically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
