External (a–h (♂); i–n (♀)): (a, i) dorsal; (b, j) lateral; (c) antenna, lateral; (d) wing; (e, k) head, dorsal; (f, l) head, frontal; (g, m) head, profile; (h, n) head, lateral. Scale bars = 1 mm (a, b, d–n); = 0.1 mm (c).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3938096" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3938096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3938096/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" startId="17.[151,250,1944,1969]" targetBox="[345,1246,189,1909]" targetPageId="17">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1944,2041]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,288,1944,1969]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">FIGURE 10.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Yeates, 2020" authorityName="Li &amp; Yeates" authorityYear="2020" box="[295,491,1945,1969]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Meomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hortorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[295,491,1945,1969]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Meomyia hortorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[498,579,1945,1969]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[498,579,1945,1969]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Genitalia (a–e (♂); f, g (♀)): (a) genital capsule, dorsal; (b) genital capsule, ventral; (c) genital capsule, lateral; (d) epandrium, dorsal; (e) epandrium, lateral; (f) sternite 8, ventral; (g) genitalia and spermathecae. Scale bars = 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,153,1043]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,255,153,179]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Legs</emphasis>
. Legs blackish brown and mostly covered in black scales, except posterior half of femora covered in white scales and hairs, posterior face of fore and mid tibia admixed with white scales. Fore femur with one row of anterior bristles medially; mid femur with one row of anterior bristles; hind femur with one row of anteroventral bristles, and more separate bristles on apical half. Bristles and other hairs on legs brown. Fore tibia 2.2 x longer than fore basitarsus, mid tibia 2.4 x longer than mid basitarsus, hind tibia 2.5 x longer than hind basitarsus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,153,1043]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,275,332,359]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Wings</emphasis>
. Wing membrane hyaline. Cell 
<emphasis box="[639,658,334,365]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[650,658,351,365]" fontSize="6" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">5</subScript>
</emphasis>
closed; cell 
<emphasis box="[803,828,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">br</emphasis>
shorter than cell 
<emphasis box="[1027,1061,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">bm</emphasis>
, crossvein 
<emphasis box="[1191,1231,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">r-m</emphasis>
arising from base of cell 
<emphasis box="[228,262,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">dm</emphasis>
; crossvein 
<emphasis box="[389,439,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">m-m</emphasis>
0.8 x as long as crossvein 
<emphasis box="[737,777,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">r-m</emphasis>
; cell 
<emphasis box="[838,878,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">cua</emphasis>
open (
<figureCitation box="[954,1038,369,396]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1967,1992]" captionTargetBox="[160,1426,281,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,273,1942]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Meomyia hortorum sp. nov. External (a–h (♂); i–n (♀)): (a, i) dorsal; (b, j) lateral; (c) antenna, lateral; (d) wing; (e, k) head, dorsal; (f, l) head, frontal; (g, m) head, profile; (h, n) head, lateral. Scale bars = 1 mm (a, b, d–n); = 0.1 mm (c)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3938094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3938094/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Fig. 9d</figureCitation>
). Haltere stem black, knob blackish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,153,1043]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,440,467]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Integumental colour of tergites black mostly with thick pale pruinescence. Tergite 1 with dense pale yellow hairs; tergite 2 with pale yellow hairs on anterior half, and dense black hairs on posterior half; tergites 3–4 with dense white hairs; tergites 5–7 with dense black hairs, except hairs sparse medially; posterior margin of tergites 3–6 with pale yellow setae, posterior margin of tergites 2 and 7 with black setae; tergite 8 with dense white hairs. Sternites black with thick pale pruinescence, sternites covered in white scales, and with pale yellow setae on posterior margin. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[291,401,620,647]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Genitalia</emphasis>
. Epandrium anterior margin strongly concave, posterior margin strongly concave (
<figureCitation box="[1326,1424,621,648]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1944,1969]" captionTargetBox="[345,1246,189,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[332,1255,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Meomyia hortorum sp. nov. Genitalia (a–e (♂); f, g (♀)): (a) genital capsule, dorsal; (b) genital capsule, ventral; (c) genital capsule, lateral; (d) epandrium, dorsal; (e) epandrium, lateral; (f) sternite 8, ventral; (g) genitalia and spermathecae. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3938096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3938096/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Fig. 10d</figureCitation>
). Lateral margin of gonocoxite slightly curved subapically (
<figureCitation box="[799,884,657,684]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1944,1969]" captionTargetBox="[345,1246,189,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[332,1255,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Meomyia hortorum sp. nov. Genitalia (a–e (♂); f, g (♀)): (a) genital capsule, dorsal; (b) genital capsule, ventral; (c) genital capsule, lateral; (d) epandrium, dorsal; (e) epandrium, lateral; (f) sternite 8, ventral; (g) genitalia and spermathecae. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3938096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3938096/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Figs 10</figureCitation>
a–b); apex of epiphallus bifid, branch slender and acute apically (
<figureCitation box="[321,418,693,719]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1944,1969]" captionTargetBox="[345,1246,189,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[332,1255,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Meomyia hortorum sp. nov. Genitalia (a–e (♂); f, g (♀)): (a) genital capsule, dorsal; (b) genital capsule, ventral; (c) genital capsule, lateral; (d) epandrium, dorsal; (e) epandrium, lateral; (f) sternite 8, ventral; (g) genitalia and spermathecae. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3938096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3938096/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Fig. 10c</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,153,1043]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,729,755]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Female.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[443,579,729,755]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.75" metricValueMax="9.2" metricValueMin="8.3" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" unit="mm" value="8.75" valueMax="9.2" valueMin="8.3">8.3–9.2 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[728,866,728,755]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.15" metricValueMax="9.5" metricValueMin="8.8" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" unit="mm" value="9.15" valueMax="9.5" valueMin="8.8">8.8–9.5 mm</quantity>
. Very similar to male, except frons black with thick pale pruinescence, 2.9 x as wide as ocellar tubercle, frons with short white scales admixed with brownish yellow setae (
<figureCitation box="[222,307,801,828]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1967,1992]" captionTargetBox="[160,1426,281,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,273,1942]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Meomyia hortorum sp. nov. External (a–h (♂); i–n (♀)): (a, i) dorsal; (b, j) lateral; (c) antenna, lateral; (d) wing; (e, k) head, dorsal; (f, l) head, frontal; (g, m) head, profile; (h, n) head, lateral. Scale bars = 1 mm (a, b, d–n); = 0.1 mm (c)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3938094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3938094/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Fig. 9k</figureCitation>
). Eight acanthophorite spines present on each side of tergite 9+10 (
<figureCitation box="[1059,1156,801,827]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1944,1969]" captionTargetBox="[345,1246,189,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[332,1255,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Meomyia hortorum sp. nov. Genitalia (a–e (♂); f, g (♀)): (a) genital capsule, dorsal; (b) genital capsule, ventral; (c) genital capsule, lateral; (d) epandrium, dorsal; (e) epandrium, lateral; (f) sternite 8, ventral; (g) genitalia and spermathecae. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3938096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3938096/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1111,1156,801,827]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" unit="g" value="10.0">10g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="219" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,153,1043]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,837,863]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Yeates, 2020" authorityName="Li &amp; Yeates" authorityYear="2020" box="[323,540,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Meomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hortorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[323,540,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Meomyia hortorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[547,637,837,863]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[547,637,837,863]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Yeates, 2020" authorityName="Li &amp; Yeates" authorityYear="2020" box="[785,976,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Meomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kochae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[785,976,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Meomyia kochae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[984,1074,837,863]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[984,1074,837,863]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but differs as follows: antennal flagellum wide; posterior margin of scutellum and abdominal tergites 3–6 with pale yellow setae; lateral margin of male gonocoxite slightly curved subapically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
